---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
import About from '../components/About.astro';
import { getAbout } from '../lib/content';

const about = getAbout();
---

<Page title="About" description="Who Ian Brogan is — background, skills, and the story behind the range.">
  <div class="page-hero container">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <span class="rule-gold"></span>
    <h1>Who I Am.</h1>
    <p class="lead">Seven years of self-directed study. Real responsibility. A range that's a feature, not a bug.</p>
  </div>
  <About data={about} />

  <section class="books-section container">
    <div class="books-header">
      <span class="eyebrow">Reading List</span>
      <span class="rule-gold"></span>
      <h2>Books that shaped how I think.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="books-grid">

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9781982160272-L.jpg"
            alt="The Changing World Order by Ray Dalio"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Ray Dalio</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">The Changing World Order</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            History moves in cycles. Great empires rise, peak, and decline following the same pattern of debt, internal conflict, and power transition. Once you see the template, you can never look at geopolitics — or markets — the same way again.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9781501124020-L.jpg"
            alt="Principles by Ray Dalio"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Ray Dalio</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">Principles</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Build a system of principles and apply them ruthlessly and consistently. Pain plus reflection equals progress. The most successful people are those who make good decisions as a habit — not by luck, but by having a repeatable process.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9780857197689-L.jpg"
            alt="The Psychology of Money by Morgan Housel"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Morgan Housel</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">The Psychology of Money</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Wealth is built through behavior, not intelligence. Time in the market, compounding, and avoiding catastrophic mistakes matter far more than picking the right stocks. The biggest financial skill is getting out of your own way.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9780241476246-L.jpg"
            alt="Trillions by Robin Wigglesworth"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Robin Wigglesworth</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">Trillions</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Index funds and passive investing quietly rewrote the rules of finance. Understanding how the majority of capital actually moves — not through active stock pickers but through passive flows — is essential to understanding modern markets.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9781501135927-L.jpg"
            alt="Shoe Dog by Phil Knight"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Phil Knight</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">Shoe Dog</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Building something real requires irrational commitment. Nike nearly died a dozen times. What kept it alive wasn't a perfect plan — it was obsession, adaptability, and people who believed in the mission before there was proof it would work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap">
          <img
            src="https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9781585424337-L.jpg"
            alt="Think and Grow Rich by Napoleon Hill"
            class="book-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author">Napoleon Hill</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">Think and Grow Rich</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Desire, belief, and persistence are prerequisites for any outcome worth having. The clearer and more specific your goal, the more your mind works to find paths toward it — even when you're not consciously thinking about it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="book-card book-card--article">
        <div class="book-cover-wrap article-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="book-body">
          <div class="book-meta">
            <span class="book-author article-tag">Essay</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="book-title">"Capitalism Created the Climate Crisis and Capitalism Will Fix It"</h3>
          <p class="book-lesson">
            <span class="lesson-label">Key lesson —</span>
            Market incentives, properly aligned, are more powerful than regulation alone. The same system that created the problem can be redirected to solve it — if the right capital flows toward the right innovations at the right time.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Page>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(8rem, 12vw, 12rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .books-section {
    padding-block: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 6rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .books-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .books-header h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
  }

  .books-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .book-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.75rem;
    background: var(--color-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-gold);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .book-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.4), 0 0 0 1px rgba(201,162,39,0.2);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .book-cover-wrap {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 90px;
  }
  .book-cover {
    width: 90px;
    display: block;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }

  .article-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    height: 120px;
  }
  .article-tag {
    color: var(--color-muted) !important;
  }

  .book-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .book-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .book-author {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .book-title {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .book-lesson {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .lesson-label {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .book-card { flex-direction: column; }
    .book-cover-wrap { width: 70px; }
    .book-cover { width: 70px; }
  }
</style>
